trans-unit.source: The <xref:Microsoft.VisualBasic.ApplicationServices.WindowsFormsApplicationBase.Startup> event occurs when the application starts, if the application implements the Visual Basic Application Model.
For more information, see [Overview of the Visual Basic Application Model](~/docs/visual-basic/developing-apps/development-with-my/overview-of-the-visual-basic-application-model.md).
<xref:Microsoft.VisualBasic.ApplicationServices.StartupEventArgs> contains the command-line arguments of the application and indicates whether the application startup should be canceled.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="Microsoft.VisualBasic.ApplicationServices.StartupEventArgs"></xref> class.
The <xref:Microsoft.VisualBasic.ApplicationServices.WindowsFormsApplicationBase.Startup> event occurs when the application starts, if the application implements the Visual Basic Application Model.
For more information, see [Overview of the Visual Basic Application Model](~/docs/visual-basic/developing-apps/development-with-my/overview-of-the-visual-basic-application-model.md).
<xref:Microsoft.VisualBasic.ApplicationServices.StartupEventArgs> contains the command-line arguments of the application and indicates whether the application startup should be canceled.
A <xref href="System.Collections.ObjectModel.ReadOnlyCollection`1"></xref> object that contains the command-line arguments of the application.
Gets the command-line arguments of the application.
